criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Children aged between 4 and 12 years;

          -  Maintenance treatment using low dose of laxative;

          -  A family with the socio-economic culture that would make it possible to carry out the
             procedures of the study's protocol.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Children with organic cause constipation such as Hirschsprung disease, cerebral
             paralysis, anorectal and spinal medulla abnormalities and metabolic illnesses;

          -  The regular use of a fiber supplement during the 4 weeks prior to admission;

          -  The use of medications that would cause constipation;

          -  Absence of a fixed or mobile telephone in order to make contact.
